        "documentHtml": "<section style=\"margin:0 0 20px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;box-sizing:border-box;padding:22px;border-radius:22px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(246,245,255,0.99), rgba(238,233,255,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(91,33,182,0.18);box-shadow:0 14px 32px rgba(76,29,149,0.14);gap:14px;\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:flex-start;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;\"><div style=\"font:700 11px/1.2 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#6d28d9;\">Title</div><div style=\"font:700 30px/1.08 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">The Browser Bar</div></div><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:flex-end;gap:6px;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(109,40,217,0.1);color:#6d28d9;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;\">headline</span><span style=\"font:600 10px/1.2 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5b21b6;opacity:0.72;\">active</span></div></div><div style=\"height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(139,92,246,0.45), rgba(139,92,246,0));\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.65 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#4b5563;\">Learn what the address field, refresh, navigation controls, bookmarks, and browser actions are for.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 18px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Read the address before you act</div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #7c3aed, #a78bfa);\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">The large field in the browser bar tells you what graph you are in. A <code>github://...</code> address means the graph is being read from a GitHub-backed repository path. A local or temporary graph will read differently, so the address is your first clue about where edits, saves, and refreshes are really happening.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 18px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Use the controls to stay oriented</div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #7c3aed, #a78bfa);\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">Back, forward, home, and refresh are navigation and trust tools, not decoration. Bookmarks let you pin places you revisit often. The location / position / zoom indicator tells you where you are on the graph surface and how far in or out you are, which matters when a graph is larger than one screen. Clicking the indicator resets zoom to <code>1x</code>.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0 0 18px 0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(248,250,252,0.96));border:1px solid rgba(15,23,42,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(15,23,42,0.08);\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Treat hosting as the next layer</div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #7c3aed, #a78bfa);\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">The browser bar can tell you that a graph is GitHub-backed, but it does not by itself explain how that graph is hosted or published to outside users. That is a related topic. This chapter should point to the GitHub and hosting material so the reader can connect repository addresses with public delivery without mixing too many concepts into one page.</div></div></section><section style=\"margin:0;\"><div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;padding:20px;border-radius:20px;background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.99), rgba(255,245,250,0.97));border:1px solid rgba(219,39,119,0.12);box-shadow:0 12px 28px rgba(190,24,93,0.08);\"><div style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;\"><div style=\"font:700 24px/1.15 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#111827;\">Summary</div><span style=\"padding:4px 8px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(219,39,119,0.14);color:#9d174d;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;\">Summary</span></div><div style=\"height:4px;border-radius:999px;background:linear-gradient(90deg, #db2777, #f472b6);\"></div><div style=\"font:500 15px/1.7 ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif;color:#1f2937;\">The browser bar answers three beginner questions at once: where am I, how do I move, and what kind of graph is this. The GitHub/hosting side belongs nearby, but not fully inside this chapter.</div></div></section>",
        "definitionKey": "document-view",
